def: The finishing course of a wall showing above a cornice.
Not doubted; not called in question; indubitable; indisputable;as, undoubted proof; undoubted hero.-- Un*doubt"ed*ly, adv.
A euphorbiaceous shrub of the genus Pedilanthus (P.tithymaloides), found in the West Indies, and possessing powerfulemetic and drastic qualities.
. Capable of being excoriated.The scaly covering of fishes, . . . even in such as are excoriatable.Sir T. Browne.
Pertaining to, or in the region of, the lower jaw and the hyoidapparatus; as, the mylohyoid nerve.
One of the ordinaries, much like the flanch, but less roundedand therefore smaller.
A comprehensive division of the Vertebrata, including all thosethat have a skull.
Affected with darkness or dimness; dark; obscure. [R.] Blount.The caliginous regions of the air. Hallywell.-- Ca*lig"i*nous*ly, adv.-- Ca*lig"i*nous*ness, n.
